Authentication API

This API represents a series of endpoints for creating, authenticating, and preserving authorization within the scope of the Wheelwell ecosystem.

Register

The registration endpoint accepts an email and password combination and user details to generate a user account within Wheelwell using a local strategy.

Request

POST /auth/register
{
    "username": "emailaddress@gmail.com",
    "password": "1234567",
    "first_name": "John",
    "last_name": "Doe"
}

Parameters

[object Object]required
string — The user's email address.

passwordrequired
string — The user's password. Minimum 7 character length.

first_namerequired
string — The user's first name.

last_namerequired
string — The user's last name.

return_access_token
boolean — Returns an Access Token in the response body when set to true. Otherwise sets a secure cookie session.

Example Response
